cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IR 

The paper discusses user perceptions and behavior in the context of privacy in the Internet of Things (IoT). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also involves human-computer interaction (HCI), which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper discusses privacy risks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves contextualized interviews, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
